WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career, Mrs. Goode has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of her
colleagues and the citizens she so ably served; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we extend to Melinda Poteet Goode our heartfelt wishes for a happy and
fulfilling retirement, offering our deepest gratitude for her many years of distinguished service
with the Northwest Tennessee Development District and Human Resource Agency and wishing
her every continued success in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
